        {
            "id": "s_l1_3",
            "type": "text",
            "title": "The Bridge 🌉",
            "content": "JavaScript can't touch HTML directly.\n\nIt uses the **DOM** as a bridge to change the page (add text, change colors, hide things)."
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l1_4",
            "type": "tip",
            "title": "The 'document' 📄",
            "content": "## `document` Variable\n\nThe entire page is stored in a global variable called `document`.\n\nYou can access everything from there!"
        },
